meanings.definition: The act of getting rid of or doing away with; ending.
examples: The abolition of war means that countries will not fight each other any more.

meanings.definition: Devoted to study, speculation, and abstract mental activity.
examples: The intellectual student was into learning and critical thinking.

images.alt: Photo of a person reading a printed page.
images.description: A person looks down at a printed page. She leans forward and is focused on the information on the page.
images.caption: Reading is one of many intellectual activities.

meanings.definition: To cause, urge, stimulate or influence to do.
examples: My mother's kindness inspired me to write a book about her.

meanings.definition: To save for a particular purpose or person.
examples: Let's call the restaurant and reserve a table.

images.alt: Photo of a table with a sign on it that says, "Reserved."
images.description: A table set with plates and small bowls. A small sign is on the table that says, "Reserved."
images.caption: When a table is reserved, it is saved for a particular group of people.

meanings.definition: To sign up to serve in the military or in some cause.
examples: He will enlist in the army.
My brother strives to be a better piano player.
If someone could tell you your true fate, would you want to hear it?

images.alt: Photo of a person bunji jumping.
images.description: A person is in mid-air, having just leapt from a platform high above a river. The person's arms are stretched out. A long elastic cord attaches the person to the platform.  A river can be seen far below.
images.caption: A bunji cord helps this person know that his fate will be to arrive safely on the ground after a spectacular jump.

meanings.definition: Any part of a whole, or a part that can be seen as distinct in some way from the whole.
examples: A train is made up of separate sections that are joined together.

images.alt: Photo of train cars connected on a track.
images.description: Five train cars are shown connected together in a straight line.
images.caption: A long train is made up of many separate sections, or cars, connected together.

meanings.definition: A person with special knowledge who gives advice.
examples: The consultant told the couple to start saving soon for their children's education.

meanings.definition: the state or condition of being in a place at a certain time.
examples: Your presence is important to everyone in the class.

images.alt: Photo of a teacher and students working on a computer.
images.description: A teacher and two students looking at a computer screen.
images.caption: The presence of both teachers and students is important for learning!
